**1\. Improvement**

**Current:** Sign up form is accepting 8 characters of the same type, regardless of type, for a password when creating the user account, which happens both on a Laptop and on an Android phone. Using a password with only one set of characters is a great security threat.

**Request**: Introduce a requirement for passwords to contain an 8-character combination of letters, numbers and symbols.  
Under the password text field, add a small text (\<10px) saying something like:” Create a password using a combination of at least 8 characters (letters, numbers, and special characters must be used).”  
When the requirements are not met, display a message saying:” Password does not meet minimum requirement\!”

**Reason**: By introducing a requirement that password needs to have a combination of character types, we are vastly improving the security of our users.   

**2\. Improvement**

**Current:** The search filters are missing explanations, and some filters may be unclear to users who are not closely familiar with the industry. For example, while using the search filter on [https://ananas.rs/kategorije/bela-tehnika/klima-uredjaji/inverter-klime](https://ananas.rs/kategorije/bela-tehnika/klima-uredjaji/inverter-klime), we come across a dropdown menu called 'Kapacitet klima uredjaja', which offers options in the range from 9000 BTU to 24000 BTU. I didn’t understand what these labels mean or which air conditioner would be suitable for me. I assume that 90% of users who are shopping on this website also don’t know what are the meanings of these units and terms.

**Request:** Add a ![][image1] icon, which, when hovered, explains what that option is for (some kind of unit in this example)

**Reason:** By introducing explanations for product filters, we improve the overall user experience (UX) and increase the chance of customers returning to the website.

**5\. Improvement** (UI)  
**Current:** There is a lot of text in this purchasing process explanation.

**Request:** Follow the Progressive disclosure principle, and on top of the site, add a short (30- 60 sec.) video tutorial explaining the process and some common questions, but under it, make text links leading to the text about each of the subjects mentioned in the video.

**Reason:** Adding a video explanation can improve UI because you can deliver the main points of the text quickly, and the majority of users are more attracted to a short video than to a whole page of text. Using the progressive disclosure principle gives us a page that is easily scanable and accessible.
